    "summary": "Laura is currently working as a PhD Candidate at KU Leuven. Her research focuses on both structural (DWI, white & gray matter volumes and microstructure) and functional (rs-fMRI, tb-fMRI) brain changes, i.e. neuroplasticity, following training. Moreover, with her FWO aspirant fellowship she will be able to investigate if and how these neuroplasticity processes can be facilitated or boosted by sleep (measured with EEG) in healthy young adults and traumatic brain injury patients. \n\nLaura has a strong background in neuroscience and is experienced in neuroimaging (DTI) in Parkinson's Disease patients experiencing verbal fluency decline following deep brain stimulation, neurophysiology (EEG) in critically ill children experiencing clinical and/or subclinical seizures and the effect of blue-light blocking glasses on sleep quality (PSQI) and quantitiy (SQS) in adolescents (high school students). She is interested in unraveling the mysteries of the human brain, both in health and disease/pathology, i.e. neurological and neuropsychiatric/neuropsychological populations. \n\nLaura is eager to learn and has (inter)national research experiences in Amsterdam, The Netherlands (Academic Medical Center Amsterdam; Netherlands Institute for Neuroscience), Toronto, Canada (SickKids Hospital for Sick Children) and has moved to Belgium (Leuven) to expand her neuroscientific knowlegde substantially.",
