                    "company": "University of Amsterdam",
                    "description": "Literature review entitled \"Unraveling the neurobiological mechanism underlying postictal disorientation as predictor of retrograde amnesia following electroconvulsive therapy\"\n\nThe proposed model suggests the following: ECT induces an insult, which is followed by dopamine deficiency. This may cause an increase in delta and theta power in the frontotemporal regions, reflecting postictal disorientation. In turn, this cortical excitability can lead to disruption of a prior LTP, reflecting retrograde amnesia. Although the model is not yet a perfect representation of the reality, only capturing some aspects of the bigger picture, it can be used to further investigate the missing links and additional factors to be involved in the neurobiological mechanism underlying postictal disorientation in order to gain more insights in possible solutions and medication for patients to prevent them from getting retrograde amnesia following electroconvulsive therapy.\n\n\u2022 Supervisor: Esm\u00e9e Verwijk, PhD\n\u2022 Grade: 8.5/10",
                    "title": "Master's Thesis",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
